      <text>8.2.9 (Which are correct sigma notation for this sum?)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="noindent">Which of the following are correct sigma notation for the sum {@(apply("+",terms)),simp=false@}?</p>  
 [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="noindent">All the options seem to use the right general form (something like {@expr@}), so we just need to check that the upper and lower limits are correct.</p><p class="noindent">The following are all correct representations, and there are many more:</p><p class="noindent">\[ {@cor1@}\quad{@cor2@}\quad{@cor3@}\quad{@cor4@} \]</p><p></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
